# No Dead Code

After every change, scan the affected files and remove anything that is now unreachable or unused.

## What to delete

- CSS classes defined but not referenced in any HTML or added by JS
- JS variables, functions, or branches that can never execute
- HTML attributes (`id`, `data-*`, `class`) with no corresponding CSS or JS usage
- Unused imports or `require()` calls
- Server middleware or routes that no longer serve a purpose

## Examples

```js
// ❌ BAD — badge element doesn't exist in HTML, branch is dead
const badge = document.querySelector('.about__badge-num');
if (badge) animateValue(badge, parseInt(badge.dataset.target, 10));

// ✅ GOOD — removed entirely
```

```css
/* ❌ BAD — class never appears in HTML */
.btn--outline-dark { ... }
.btn--outline-dark:hover { ... }

/* ✅ GOOD — deleted */
```

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD — id never referenced by CSS or JS -->
<section class="hero" id="hero">

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<section class="hero">
```

## When to check

- After adding a new component or section — old one may be replaced
- After renaming a CSS class — old name becomes dead
- After refactoring JS logic — old branches may become unreachable
- After removing an HTML element — its styles and event listeners become dead
